                  <desc type="foundation">Local traditio tells that it was founded in the time of Aksumite King <persName ref="PRS3729ellaAm">ʾAlʿāmedā</persName> and re-stablished by St. <persName ref="PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Haymanot</persName> (d. 1313).</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Dabr. The area is said to have formerly been the place of monks and hermits. Currently, a few nuns live at the church; there are indeed traces of monks' presense in the gourge around the church.  &#xD;
</ab>
